{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1012823&cite=26USCAS167&originatingDoc=I235957fb9c1e11d9bdd1cfdd544ca3a4&refType=RB&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)#co_pp_8b3b0000958a4" }{\fldrslt 
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf5 \i0 
Section 167(a) of the Internal Revenue Code of 1954
}}}
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf1 \i0 
 allows a depreciation deduction from gross income for \u8216\'3fproperty used in the (taxpayer\rquote s) trade or business\rquote  or \u8216\'3fheld for the production of income,\u8217\'3f whereas 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=26USCAS263&originatingDoc=I235957fb9c1e11d9bdd1cfdd544ca3a4&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf5 \i0 
s 263(a)(1)
}}}
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf1 \i0 
 of the Code disallows a deduction for \u8216\'3f(a)ny amount paid out for new buildings or for permanent improvements or betterments made to increase the value of any property or estate,\u8217\'3f expenditures which, the regulations state, include the \u8216\'3fcost of acquisition, construction, or erection of buildings.\u8217\'3f 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=26USCAS161&originatingDoc=I235957fb9c1e11d9bdd1cfdd544ca3a4&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf5 \i0 
Section 161
}}}
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf1 \i0 
 makes the deductions specified in that part of the Code, including 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1012823&cite=26USCAS167&originatingDoc=I235957fb9c1e11d9bdd1cfdd544ca3a4&refType=RB&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)#co_pp_8b3b0000958a4" }{\fldrslt 
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf5 \i0 
s 167(a)
}}}
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf1 \i0 
, subject to the exceptions provided in the part including 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=26USCAS263&originatingDoc=I235957fb9c1e11d9bdd1cfdd544ca3a4&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf5 \i0 
s 263
}}}
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf1 \i0 
. Respondent public utility claimed a deduction from gross income under 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1012823&cite=26USCAS167&originatingDoc=I235957fb9c1e11d9bdd1cfdd544ca3a4&refType=RB&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)#co_pp_8b3b0000958a4" }{\fldrslt 
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf5 \i0 
s 167(a)
}}}
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf1 \i0 
 for all the depreciation for the year on its transportation equipment (cars, trucks, etc.), including that portion attributable to its use in constructing capital facilities, although on its books, as required by the regulatory agencies, it charged such equipment, to the extent it was used in construction, to the capital assets so constructed. The Commissioner of Internal Revenue disallowed the deduction for the construction-related depreciation, ruling that that depreciation was a nondeductible capital expenditure under 
}
{\f2 \b1 \fs20 \cf1 \i0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_780_2_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_780_2_1}
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b1 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf1 \i0 
